{
  "texts": [
    "In particular, we demonstrate that the objective functions of DPO under the BT assumption can be characterized as special cases of a mutual information maximization objective, using InfoNCE (Oord et al., 2018) as the estimator.",
    "Building on this insight, we propose a novel method that learns an effective policy from preference data without relying on the BT assumption.",
    "Specifically, InfoPO leverages the NWJ estimator (Nguyen et al., 2010) for mutual information estimation instead of InfoNCE.",
    "Intuitively, InfoPO weights the log likelihood of rejected responses according to model probability and uses an exponential operation to control the gradient norms towards rejected responses.",
    "We show that InfoPO enables the model to update conservatively in the direction of rejected responses, while preventing a decrease in the likelihood of chosen responses."
  ]
}